## `system.getEnv(name)`

Get the value of an environment variable.

### Parameters
- **name** (string, optional): Name of the environment variable. If omitted, returns all environment variables.

### Return Value
The value of the environment variable, or `null` if it doesn't exist. If no parameter is provided, returns an object containing all environment variables.

{% aside type="tip" %}

Omitting the parameter will return all environment variables.
```js
var allEnv = system.getEnv();
```
{% /aside %}

## Examples

### Getting a Specific Environment Variable

```javascript
// Get the PATH environment variable
var path = system.getEnv("PATH");
novadesk.log("Current PATH: " + path);

// Get the username
var username = system.getEnv("USERNAME");
novadesk.log("Current user: " + username);

// Get the TEMP directory
var tempDir = system.getEnv("TEMP");
novadesk.log("Temp directory: " + tempDir);
```

### Getting All Environment Variables

```javascript
// Get all environment variables as an object
var allEnv = system.getEnv();
novadesk.log("Total environment variables: " + Object.keys(allEnv).length);

// Iterate through all environment variables
for (var key in allEnv) {
    if (allEnv.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
        novadesk.log(key + " = " + allEnv[key]);
    }
}
```